"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses the `sns.lmplot` function within the `g.map()` method. The `map()` function is intended to apply a plotting function that takes the x and y variables as arguments, but `lmplot` is a figure-level function and cannot be used in this context. Instead, a lower-level function like `sns.regplot` should be used.\",\n  \"patch\": \"6c6\\n< g.map(sns.lmplot, 'total_bill', 'tip')\\n---\\n> g.map(sns.regplot, 'total_bill', 'tip')\"\n}"